browser->server: HTTP POST https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/new_note

note over server:
server executes js-code that creates a new note object and adds it to the "notes" array
end note

server-->browser: URL Redirect (302)
browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/main.css
server-->browser: main.css
browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/main.js
server-->browser: main.js

note over browser:
browser starts executing js-code that requests JSON data from server, containing the new note
end note

browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/data.json
server-->browser: [{ content: "HTML is easy", date: "2019-05-23" }, ...]

note over browser:
browser executes the event handler
that renders notes to display
end note
